## Schema Conventions (CRITICAL)

**Before creating any migration, ensure your schema follows these conventions:**

### Timestamp Fields - ALWAYS Use @updatedAt

```prisma
// ✅ CORRECT - Auto-managed timestamps
model YourModel {
  id        Int      @id @default(autoincrement())
  createdAt DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt  // REQUIRED
}

// ❌ WRONG - Will cause TypeScript build errors
model YourModel {
  id        Int      @id @default(autoincrement())
  createdAt DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt DateTime  // Missing @updatedAt
}
```

**Why this matters:**
- Without `@updatedAt`, developers must manually provide `updatedAt: new Date()` in every create/update
- Forgetting this causes TypeScript build errors
- `@updatedAt` makes the field optional and auto-managed

**See:** `.cursor/rules/database-patterns.mdc` for complete Prisma schema conventions

