## 5.5 Automated Drift Detection (Recommended)

### Pre-Commit Hook

Prevent commits when schema is out of sync with database:

**Setup (.husky/pre-commit):**
```bash
#!/bin/sh

# Check if DATABASE_URL is available
if [ -z "$DATABASE_URL" ]; then
  echo "⚠️  DATABASE_URL not set, skipping schema sync check"
  exit 0
fi

# Check for schema drift
echo "Checking Prisma schema sync..."
npx prisma db pull --print > /tmp/prisma-schema-check 2>&1

if ! diff -q prisma/schema.prisma /tmp/prisma-schema-check > /dev/null; then
  echo ""
  echo "❌ Schema drift detected!"
  echo "Your schema.prisma doesn't match the database."
  echo ""
  echo "Run: npx prisma db pull"
  echo "Then review and commit changes."
  exit 1
fi

echo "✅ Schema is in sync"
```

